# Provisioning Audit Log

Provisioning runs must append an entry to the audit log, mirroring the deprovision log pattern.

## Log File

- **Path**: `provision_log.json` at project root (configurable via `--log-file`)
- **Order**: Latest at top (processed date descending) — use `insert(0, entry)`

## Entry Format

```json
{
  "timestamp": "ISO8601",
  "org": "mavenprod",
  "source": "csv",
  "csv_file": "path/to/users.csv",
  "success": 2,
  "failed": 0,
  "details": [
    {"name": "John Doe", "email": "...", "username": "...", "status": "created", "userId": "..."},
    {"name": "Jane Doe", "email": "...", "status": "failed", "error": "..."}
  ]
}
```

## Details Status Values

- `created` — user provisioned successfully
- `failed` — provisioning failed (include `error`)
